<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="adapthisteq" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><refnamediv><refname>adapthisteq</refname><refpurpose>Apply adaptive histogram equalization.</refpurpose></refnamediv><refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = adapthisteq(image); out = adapthisteq(image, clipLimit)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Grayscale or RGB image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>clipLimit</term><listitem><para>Positive CLAHE clip limit. Default is 3.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection><refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>adapthisteq</function> is a MATLAB-style compatibility entry point for <function>imadapthistequal</function>, which provides IPCV CLAHE processing and supports RGB input.</para></refsection><refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[image = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/baboon.png")); out = adapthisteq(image, 3); imshow(out);]]></programlisting></refsection><refsection role="see also"><title>See also</title><simplelist type="inline"><member><link linkend="imadapthistequal">imadapthistequal</link></member><member><link linkend="imhistequal">imhistequal</link></member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>Authors</title><simplelist type="vert"><member>Tan Chin Luh</member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>History</title><informaltable border="1"><tr><td>Version</td><td>Description</td></tr><tr><td>5.0.0</td><td>Compatibility entry point introduced in development Step 3.</td></tr></informaltable></refsection></refentry>
